TRIVIA

Trivia

The series names 6 protocols to be followed by Travelers that are referenced throughout the series: 1. The mission comes first. 2. Never jeopardize your cover. 3. Don't take a life, don't save a life, unless otherwise directed. 4. Do not reproduce. 5. In the absence of direction, maintain your host's life. 6. No inter-team or deep web communication except in extreme emergencies.

The names of the horses mentioned by Philip are all gun names from video game Destiny. Patience and Time, The Last Word, Touch of Malice, The Fourth Horsemen are exotic guns, Down and Doubt is a legendary hand cannon. Season 2 also features Outbreak Prime and Gjallerhorn as the names of race dogs.

David's clock in the show also makes an appearance in another time travelling show, Continuum.

T.E.L.L. stands for time, elevation, latitude, and longitude. It is the precise time and location of death used by the director, as well as historical records and social media, to determine who will become a host for the travelers.

As of the end of season 3, there have been non-consecutive episodes entitled Protocol 6, Protocol 5, Protocol 4, and Protocol 3. Interestingly, they have aired in this descending order, in the style of a countdown.
